CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Breakfast At The Pooles - Mr. and Mrs. W.T. Poole entertained several members of the United Supreme Council 33 decree Scottish Rite Masons, PHM, during their stay in Pittsburgh... Right photo, seated: Miss Martha Tyson, Mrs. Wilbur C. Douglass, Mrs. Forrest Parr, George W. Crawford, Most Sovereign Grand Commander, New Haven, Conn.; Mrs. Poole, the hostess; William A. Heathman, treasurer of the Council, Providence, R.I.; Mrs. Samuel Parr, Mrs. A. P. Knott, James Robinson, Atty. Byrd Brown.  Standing:  Atty. Wilbur C. Douglass, a Council member, and Forrest Parr. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: United Supreme Council 33 degree Scottish Rite Masons and guests from left, seated: Martha Tyson, Mrs. Wilbur C. Douglass, Mrs. Forrest Parr, George W. Crawford, Mrs. W. T. Poole, William A. Heathman, Mrs. Samuel Parr, Mrs. A. P. Knott, James Robinson, and Atty. Byrd Brown; standing: Atty. Wilbur C. Douglass and Forrest Parr, gathered around table in home of Mr. and Mrs. W.T. Poole, another version
